<main class="container">
  <h2>What is SDLC?</h2>
  <p>
    The Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) is a process used to design,
    develop, test, and maintain software systems. It provides structure for
    building software efficiently and with higher quality.
  </p>

  <section class="card">
    <h3>Main Approaches</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Waterfall</li>
      <li>Agile</li>
      <li>DevOps</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h3>Why SDLC Matters</h3>
    <p>
      SDLC helps teams organize work, reduce risk, improve collaboration,
      and deliver software that better meets user needs.
    </p>
  </section>
</main>

